    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "95097384_36bc4c1a",
        "filename": "snapshot/linux/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 24
      },
      "lineNbr": 392,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-30T22:07:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Looks like the kernel’s own loader doesn’t update anything. Does the user-space loader update these values in things that the kernel’s loader loaded (including the loader itself?) or do we need to be aware of who loaded an image?",
      "revId": "ba3472105c0496ec7447e72c8ea1318c1dfe8674",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7e22f7d4_de1774c6",
        "filename": "snapshot/linux/elf_image_reader.cc",
        "patchSetId": 24
      },
      "lineNbr": 392,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-01T23:31:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The user-space glibc loader updates the dynamic section for most architectures (not MIPS).\nhttps://sourceware.org/git/?p\u003dglibc.git;a\u003dblob;f\u003delf/get-dynamic-info.h;h\u003d7525c3a5b20b5619aeda35b5f7b9849f9dfcad39;hb\u003dHEAD#l79\n\nIt looks like it does update it\u0027s own dynamic section:\nhttps://sourceware.org/git/?p\u003dglibc.git;a\u003dblob;f\u003delf/rtld.c;h\u003d65647fb1c8167ac7432c212975e4027f2c46b560;hb\u003dHEAD#l489\n\nBut yeah, we probably do need to determine whether the loader is glibc or not.\nAfter a quick look through GDB source, I suspect Android only updates DT_DEBUG because that is the only tag that GDB uses.",
      "parentUuid": "95097384_36bc4c1a",
      "revId": "ba3472105c0496ec7447e72c8ea1318c1dfe8674",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8631294c_7553e81a",
